David Rees wrote:
> What happens if your run hdparm -t /dev/hda and /dev/hdc at the same time?
Try 'hdparm -tT'  with simultaneous /dev/hda3 and /dev/hdc3.  This gives you
a baseline on the actual partitions involved.
